<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{9}{y}={0}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6}{x}-{7}{y}=-{4}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{4}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -6. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{6}}{{-{{9}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{6}}}{{-{{9}}}}{\left(-{9}{x}+{9}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{6}}}{{-{{9}}}}{\left({0}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({6}\right)}{x}+{6}{y}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{x}-{7}{y}=-{4}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{y}=-{4}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{4}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={4}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{9}{\left({4}\right)}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{\left({36}\right)}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}={0}-{\left({36}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}=-{36}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{36}}{{-{{9}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{4}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

